  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil the kettle&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Finely chop the <strong>smoked streaky</strong>&nbsp;<strong>bacon</strong></p>\r\n<p>Dice the<strong> brown&nbsp;</strong><strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Slice the <strong>courgette<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;into rounds&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/764_764_..step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/764_764_..step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/764_764_..step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/764_764_..step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/764_764_..step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a wide-based pot (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced&nbsp;onion</strong> and&nbsp;<strong>chopped&nbsp;</strong><strong>bacon</strong> and cook for 5-7 min</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>courgette</strong>&nbsp;to the pan for another 2-3 mins or until soft and lightly coloured</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/764_764_..step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/764_764_..step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/764_764_..step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/764_764_..step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/764_764_..step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>linguine</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Cook the <strong>linguine</strong> for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p>\r\n<p>Once done, drain the <strong>linguine</strong>, reserving 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/764_764_..step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/764_764_..step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/764_764_..step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/764_764_..step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/764_764_..step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>courgette</strong> is lightly browned, add the <strong>cherry&nbsp;</strong><strong>tomatoes</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>dried oregano </strong>and<strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong>chilli flakes</strong> (Can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 1 min</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/764_764_..step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
